  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n[GitHub section](https://quarkus.io/version/main/guides/security-openid-connect-web-authentication#integration-with-github-and-other-oauth2-providers) does not say that `quarkus-oidc` generates an internal `IdToken` to compensate for the fact GitHub does not itself provide it but this internal `IdToken` has no useful data and is only used to keep the common flow working as well as avoid redirecting the users every time.\r\n\r\n### Implementation ideas\r\n\r\nDocs should be improved and explain why `IdToken` is visible in the GitHub flows. (sorry @FroMage  :-) ).\r\n\r\nAlso, Steph's idea to augment it should be doc-ed - but using `UserInfo` to create a simple `Principal` instead of this `IdToken`.\r\n\r\nAdditionally, more information should be provided how to cache `UserInfo` responses",
